Gordon Mohr wrote:

&gt; I didn&#39;t want to risk any changes to robots handling in the final days
&gt; leading to release 1.14.0, but have since implemented support for the
&gt; &#39;Crawl-Delay&#39; and &#39;Allow&#39; robots.txt directives in the heritrix1 codebase.
&gt;
&gt; A new setting on the frontier, &#39;respect-crawl-delay&#39;, default value
&gt; true, will make a &#39;Crawl-Delay&#39; value found that applies to the
&gt; crawler&#39;s User-Agent an absolute floor for delays between request. (EG,
&gt; if you have a &#39;max-delay-ms&#39; of 10000ms, then encounter a Crawl-Delay of
&gt; 20 seconds, the 20 seconds wins out.)
&gt;
&gt; The feature has received cursory testing.
&gt;
&gt; The first build in which it appears is #245 from the CruiseControl auto
&gt; builds:
&gt;
&gt; http://builds.archive.org:8080/cruisecontrol/buildresults/HEAD-heritrix 
&gt; &lt;http://builds.archive.org:8080/cruisecontrol/buildresults/HEAD-heritrix&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Support for &#39;Allow&#39; and &#39;Crawl-Delay&#39; will be ported to the heritrix2
&gt; codebase shortly.
&gt;
&gt; - Gordon @ IA
&gt;
&gt; Gordon Mohr wrote:
&gt; &gt; joehung302 wrote:
&gt; &gt;&gt; I&#39;m bringing up this issue again.
&gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; First of all, we&#39;re now doing repeatable 5B+ crawling using Heritrix.
&gt; &gt;&gt; Thanks to you guys.
&gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; These days we&#39;ve got quite a few complaints about Heritrix not
&gt; &gt;&gt; honoring the &quot;crawl-delay&quot; parameter. Is this still a planned feature?
&gt; &gt;&gt;
&gt; &gt;&gt; Or, how can we help to make it happen? ;)
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; As this only requires shuttling an externally-provided number into the
&gt; &gt; existing min-delay-ms setting, it should be pretty simple, but was
&gt; &gt; overlooked as we prioritized issues for 1.14. I&#39;ll take a look soon.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; I&#39;ll also use this as a chance to remind people that they can vote for
&gt; &gt; bugs they&#39;d like fixed via the JIRA issue tracker for Heritrix:
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; http://webteam.archive.org/jira/browse/HER?report=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.project:popularissues-panel 
&gt; &lt;http://webteam.archive.org/jira/browse/HER?report=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.project:popularissues-panel&gt;
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; Part of issue triage leading up to any release is reviewing the popular
&gt; &gt; issues, in case there are things we haven&#39;t prioritized internally that
&gt; &gt; are still important to the wider community.
&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; - Gordon @ IA
